04:22.100 --> 04:23.720
Tom shayes.

04:23.730 --> 04:25.640
Why didn't he go
through with the payoff?

04:25.660 --> 04:28.480
He said his conscience
got the better of him.

04:28.510 --> 04:30.150
At the last second?

04:30.160 --> 04:32.950
And patty took him off
the infant mortality case.

04:32.960 --> 04:35.390
- Right before he made the deal.
- Yeah,I know.

04:35.400 --> 04:39.480
I was wondering the same thing,but I don't see how
patty could have known that we were setting tom up.

04:39.490 --> 04:44.710
I think she just wants him on
the purcell case. Excuse me.

04:46.040 --> 04:47.950
What have you guys found on purcell?

04:47.960 --> 04:49.620
We're gonna have to
to put a pin in that.

04:49.630 --> 04:53.810
What? Why? I told you it's the only
thing patty cares about right now.

04:53.820 --> 04:56.450
You have to lay low,ellen.

04:56.460 --> 04:58.720
We need intel.

04:58.730 --> 05:00.700
Why the shayes thing went sideways.

05:00.720 --> 05:05.030
This is just to make sure that we're all
okay cover-wise before we move forward.

05:05.050 --> 05:07.890
My cover's fine. Patty
doesn't suspect a thing.

05:07.900 --> 05:10.490
Just let me see what
I can get on purcell.

05:10.500 --> 05:15.220
Ellen,I know it's frustrating,but
we need you to back off.

05:15.240 --> 05:17.440
We're all gonna leave it alone.

05:17.910 --> 05:22.150
Okay? We'll be in touch.

05:29.340 --> 05:31.830
Don't worry. It's insulin.

05:37.560 --> 05:39.480
I'm a diabetic.

05:39.490 --> 05:40.410
Patty will be here in a minute.

05:40.420 --> 05:43.980
She wanted me to brief you before
your meeting with detective huntley.

05:43.990 --> 05:45.150
Some coffee?

05:45.160 --> 05:47.490
No,thank you.

05:50.720 --> 05:56.630
so,the preliminary autopsy report suggests
that your wife died by strangulation.

05:57.110 --> 06:01.420
There were no signs of sexual
assault,but clearly,there was A...

06:02.190 --> 06:06.430
A... there was A... struggle.

06:18.940 --> 06:22.360
Didn't the police find any
evidence of the guy who killed her?

06:22.900 --> 06:25.410
I'm afraid not.

06:29.560 --> 06:33.460
Patty,I was wondering if I could sit in
on your meeting with detective huntley?

06:33.470 --> 06:34.550
Why?

06:34.590 --> 06:37.880
I thought it would be valuable. I don't
have any experience with criminal law.

06:39.540 --> 06:42.500
I don't think mr. Purcell would
be comfortable with you there.

06:42.510 --> 06:46.050
- Okay.
- And I'm not running a law school.

06:47.780 --> 06:49.580
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

06:49.590 --> 06:53.970
Mr. Purcell,you filed a police
report,um,several days before the murder,

06:54.000 --> 06:57.590
saying that someone
broke into your house.

06:57.600 --> 06:59.420
That is correct.

06:59.430 --> 07:02.370
Um,was anything stolen on that occasion?

07:02.380 --> 07:04.210
No.

07:04.230 --> 07:07.060
My daughter heard the
intruder and woke me.

07:07.070 --> 07:10.750
We must have chased him out before
he had time to steal anything.

07:11.170 --> 07:15.600
And-and the second intruder-- the
one you believe killed your wife--

07:15.610 --> 07:18.370
he didn't steal anything,either.

07:20.160 --> 07:23.100
Not to my knowledge,no.

07:23.110 --> 07:26.970
Do you think it was the
same man on both occasions?

07:26.980 --> 07:28.410
It could have been.

07:28.420 --> 07:30.380
The first time,it was dark.

07:30.410 --> 07:34.520
He was wearing a hooded sweatshirt.

07:35.830 --> 07:38.340
I really didn'T... see his face.

07:38.350 --> 07:42.000
Right. Well,I read that in the
report. It's just so curious.

07:42.010 --> 07:46.870
You know,two home invasions in
one week,and yet nothing's missing.

07:48.890 --> 07:52.970
You know,late last night,I
was struck by the thought,um,

07:52.980 --> 07:55.760
did someone target the wrong house?

07:55.770 --> 07:59.630
Oh,isn't it your job to
figure that out,detective?

07:59.660 --> 08:00.720
Right,right.

08:00.730 --> 08:05.930
Um,okay,well,describe the man that you
saw the night of the-the second break-in.

08:05.940 --> 08:09.530
I have. Several times.

08:09.540 --> 08:11.490
Right. Let's see.

08:11.500 --> 08:14.070
Shorter than mr. Purcell.

08:14.080 --> 08:18.720
Um,stringy blond hair. A
long-sleeved t-shirt,possibly jeans.

08:19.050 --> 08:24.690
You know,forgive me. I'm just stuck on why someone
would break into a house twice and not steal anything.

08:25.360 --> 08:28.600
There wasn't enough
time to steal anything.

08:29.680 --> 08:33.230
There was barely
enough time to kill her.

08:40.909 --> 08:44.630
May I show you some photos
taken at the crime scene?

08:45.370 --> 08:49.730
I mean,I'M... I'm afraid this
may be difficult to look at.

08:51.470 --> 08:53.740
Anything to help.

08:53.750 --> 08:56.110
We'll see if you see something in
the photos that jogs your memory.

08:56.130 --> 08:58.760
Mr. Purcell isn't here
to be harassed,detective.

08:58.770 --> 09:01.150
He's here to find the
man who killed his wife.

09:01.160 --> 09:02.330
No. It's okay,patty.

09:02.340 --> 09:07.110
Daniel,you do not have to do this.

09:07.120 --> 09:11.230
I'm here to help. I want to do this.

09:30.320 --> 09:32.880
You're okay to continue?

09:32.890 --> 09:38.850
Yeah,I think... I... I think so.

09:41.910 --> 09:45.110
Is there anything out of the ordinary?

10:00.930 --> 10:02.120
No.

10:02.130 --> 10:05.360
Are those the clothes that she
was wearing earlier in the night?

10:06.440 --> 10:08.760
Yes. She was dressed for the gala.

10:08.770 --> 10:11.050
I don't believe you
know my wife christine.

10:11.080 --> 10:14.340
It's really nice to meet you.
I admire your work so much.

10:14.350 --> 10:16.240
Thank you for your support.

10:16.250 --> 10:20.790
What about the kitchen? Was there anything
out of place or different than usual?

10:20.800 --> 10:22.800
No.

10:25.410 --> 10:28.370
What is it,daniel?

10:30.520 --> 10:32.750
What do you see?

10:33.200 --> 10:34.690
Her ring.

10:34.720 --> 10:37.740
- Excuse me?
- Her ring.

10:39.210 --> 10:42.100
She's not wearing it.

10:43.680 --> 10:47.590
I gave it to her on our tenth
anniversary. It's a ruby.

10:48.140 --> 10:50.450
An heirloom.

10:50.470 --> 10:52.080
She always wore it.

10:52.090 --> 10:54.670
- On which hand?
- The right.

10:55.100 --> 11:00.840
Oh,so they stole the
ruby and left the diamond?

11:03.200 --> 11:05.460
Is this the first time
you noticed it missing?

11:06.020 --> 11:09.130
Yes.

11:10.000 --> 11:11.410
Obviously.

11:11.420 --> 11:13.980
This is a very important
development,mr. Purcell.

11:13.990 --> 11:18.610
It is... a big development.

11:19.150 --> 11:22.260
- Yeah,I made a note of it.
- Listen,asshole.

11:23.100 --> 11:26.060
You find that ring,and
you find my wife's killer.

11:26.070 --> 11:28.240
Daniel,calm down.

11:28.250 --> 11:34.670
If you think i killed
her,then just say it!

11:37.070 --> 11:39.640
And we'll know where we stand.

11:39.650 --> 11:41.510
Mr. Purcell,i believe you.

11:41.520 --> 11:42.770
Really?

11:42.780 --> 11:46.640
Because the man who murdered
christine is still out there,

11:46.970 --> 11:49.940
and you have been absolutely useless.

11:49.970 --> 11:52.800
Can we have a few
moments,please,detective?

11:52.810 --> 11:54.630
Oh,sure.

11:55.580 --> 11:56.820
Thank you.

11:56.830 --> 11:59.730
Um,one last question... if I could.

11:59.740 --> 12:03.640
Um,did you ever lay hands on your wife?

12:03.650 --> 12:06.340
Of course not.

12:07.320 --> 12:11.470
Well,according to the state of
new york,she claims otherwise.

12:11.480 --> 12:14.620
Your wife filed a
complaint three years ago.

12:17.660 --> 12:18.960
Where did you get that?

12:19.000 --> 12:24.020
Oh,the same file i found the restraining
order that she had issued against you.

12:24.030 --> 12:25.930
I think we're through here,detective.

12:25.940 --> 12:27.840
- Where did you get those documents?
- Daniel.

12:27.850 --> 12:30.610
Because these were
sealed under court order.

12:30.650 --> 12:32.870
You can't use these against me.

12:32.890 --> 12:35.510
Can you explain the assault
from three years ago?

12:35.540 --> 12:37.060
- Don't answer that.
- No,no,no,no.

12:37.070 --> 12:39.520
- Absolutely,I can explain it.
- Detective,I'm gonna ask you to step out.

12:39.530 --> 12:42.760
- I want to answer this guy.
- Daniel,no!

12:43.080 --> 12:46.260
Don't manage me. I'm
not a goddamned child.

12:46.270 --> 12:49.750
Stop acting like one.

12:50.230 --> 12:53.590
Just shut your mouth and do as i say.

12:53.600 --> 12:57.240
I'm sorry. Uh,do you need a minute?

13:01.610 --> 13:03.600
A restraining order?

13:03.610 --> 13:05.900
How the hell did we screw that up?

13:05.930 --> 13:07.650
It didn't come up on a background check.

13:07.690 --> 13:09.230
Purcell was right.

13:09.240 --> 13:11.570
It was sealed in family court.

13:11.580 --> 13:14.960
I swear to god,he's acting
like he wants to get arrested.

13:14.980 --> 13:18.810
One incident like this three
years ago is not probable cause.

13:18.850 --> 13:22.900
No,but it looks like he's
lying about everything.

13:22.930 --> 13:25.560
I mean,two break-ins,nothing stolen.

13:25.590 --> 13:28.290
Now this new story about a ring.

13:28.300 --> 13:30.110
You don't believe it?

13:30.120 --> 13:32.330
I don't know.

13:32.340 --> 13:35.550
Why don't we turn him over to
a criminal defense attorney?

13:35.560 --> 13:38.290
We'll go after ultima
national resources ourselves.

13:38.320 --> 13:42.040
Because ultima national is bulletproof.

13:42.050 --> 13:46.500
The only way we're gonna get to them
is by having someone on the inside.

13:48.040 --> 13:51.220
I believe daniel has the answers.

14:24.650 --> 14:28.070
